From: Daniel Pawlik <pawlik.dan@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 16 Mar 2026 12:00:00 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 2/6] net: bridge: forward path helpers and VLAN modes

Add bridge flow offload helpers that expose the bridge state needed by
nft_flow_offload without requiring callers to include br_private.h:
 - br_fdb_has_forwarding_entry_rcu(): check if a MAC can be forwarded
 - br_vlan_get_offload_info_rcu(): get VLAN id and protocol
 - br_vlan_is_enabled_rcu(): check if VLAN filtering is active

Add DEV_PATH_BR_VLAN_KEEP_HW path type for switchdev-backed bridge
ports where tagged VLANs are kept in hardware without software
stripping.

Allow br_fill_forward_path() to handle port-to-port traffic by
accepting bridge port devices as ctx->dev, using the port's VLAN
group for PVID resolution.

Signed-off-by: Daniel Pawlik <pawlik.dan@gmail.com>
